content: I have got a mini deck of steampunk which does not include the book. This app is a very good complimentary to the deck and it's so handy that I can learn and use it anywhere anytime.

Far more detailed and thoughtful text accompanies each card than is found in most decks. The Knights are ladies, which isn't how I was used to reading them (the female warriors of the deck, imo, are Strength, the Queen of Swords, and sometimes, the Queen of Wands). Unusual artwork, with a intriguing spin on the Devil card!

Amazing!! This is my favorite tarot deck of all time and I'd never used a tarot app before last month. The book is so well-written and the deck illustrations are so spot on. I've use tarot almost daily for divination and meditation for years, so this is perfect for when it's not convenient to carry a deck of cards and a book around with me...my phone is always in my pocket. ;) As far as rating the app, it's just like the physical deck and book in an easy to use and intuitive format.
I am absolutely in LOVE with this app & I've had it going on 5 years. I use it every day to gain a little insight & I've read for others as well with fascinating results

Would give this 5 stars but it is missing one key reading,  which is the meaning of reversed cards.  The witch tarot set has it.  Disappointed that this didn't. This is the only reason I didn't give it 5 stars. Beautiful graphics and very nice ebook of the card meanings.
The artwork is great and the card explanations are more to the point than the other tarot apps I have. This has become my go to app.

replyContent: Barbara Moore says, "Reversals never clicked with me. They're so arbitrary. Because I don't use them, I don't create reversed meanings. If you already read reversed cards, then apply your own interpretations. Consider what they mean & apply that rather than memorizing definitions. I recommend Mary K. Greer‚Äôs "Complete Book of Tarot Reversals.""

replyContent: Barbara Moore does not provide reversed meanings for this deck. If you want to use reversed meanings, we recommend "The Complete Book of Tarot Reversals" by Mary K. Greer.

content: This one of my favorite decks. The messages are well written and clean.

I rarely install apps on my phone, but the artwork was just too mesmerizing to pass up. It allows for card reversals, which is kindof a useless feature if you aren't already accustomed to reading Tarot, as the descriptions do not differ one way or the other.
Great app I love it!

I was already a big fan, having owned the deck and booklet, and this does justice to the deck, the app is detailed and the artwork beautifully presented, and the joirnal is fantastic for revisiting previous reads and cross referencing.
